<details>
	<summary>What do the three test categories check?</summary>
	<div>
		<ul class="keep-ls">
			<li><b>Cosmetic Filter</b>: whether empty ad boxes, cookie banners and similar elements are hidden or removed.</li>
			<li><b>Script Loading</b>: whether ad scripts and trackers are stopped from loading.</li>
			<li><b>Host</b>: whether domains that serve trackers, analytics or ads are blocked.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</details>
<details>
	<summary>What do &ldquo;Blocked&rdquo; and &ldquo;Not Blocked&rdquo; mean?</summary>
	<div>
		<div class="row keep-width">
			<div>
				<div class="card _h-100">
					<div class="_f-center">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" stroke-width="2" stroke="var(--green)" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" stroke="none"></path><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"></circle><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4"></path></svg>
						&nbsp; <b>Blocked</b>
					</div>
					The connection to a host or script failed, or an ad box was removed, so your ad blocker caught it.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div>
				<div class="card _h-100">
					<div class="_f-center">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" stroke-width="2" stroke="var(--red)" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" stroke="none"></path><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"></circle><path d="M10 10l4 4m0-4l-4 4"></path></svg>
						&nbsp; <b>Not Blocked</b>
					</div>
					The connection went through, or the box stayed in place, so that item was not filtered by your setup.
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</details>
<details>
	<summary>How is my score calculated, and what do the colors mean?</summary>
	<div>
		<p>When the tests finish you get a liquid-filled score ball. Points come from how many checks your setup blocks in each category, and the fill color shows your range:</p>
		<div class="template_wrap row keep-width">
			<div>
				<div class="lt_cwrap lt_template" style="--liquid-color:var(--red);--liquid-percentage:10%">
					<div class="lt_circle">
						<div class="lt_wave"></div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div>
				<div class="lt_cwrap lt_template" style="--liquid-color:var(--orange);--liquid-percentage:0%">
					<div class="lt_circle">
						<div class="lt_wave"></div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div>
				<div class="lt_cwrap lt_template" style="--liquid-color:var(--green);--liquid-percentage:-30%">
					<div class="lt_circle">
						<div class="lt_wave"></div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row keep-width">
			<div>
				<div class="lt_value_2 _bg-red">Your ad blocker may not be enabled or configured</div>
			</div>
			<div>
				<div class="lt_value_2 _bg-orange">Okay, but you can do better</div>
			</div>
			<div>
				<div class="lt_value_2 _bg-green">Great, you're ready to surf</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</details>
<details>
	<summary>Which ad blockers and DNS filters do you recommend?</summary>
	<div>
		<p>I use <a id="dnsfilter-link" href="https://www.dnsfilter.com/">DNSFilter</a> as my main DNS resolver, with <a href="https://nextdns.io/">NextDNS</a> as a great alternative for home users. On top of that I run these combos per platform:</p>
		<ul class="keep-ls">
			<li>Windows: Brave + uBlock Origin</li>
			<li>macOS: Brave + uBlock Origin</li>
			<li>Android: Kiwi Browser + uBlock Origin</li>
			<li>iOS: Brave with built-in ad blocking, or Safari + AdGuard extension</li>
		</ul>
		<div class="_cnt-grid-wrap">
			<a href="https://ublockorigin.com/" class="btn">uBlock Origin</a>
			<a href="https://adguard.com/adguard-ios/overview.html" class="btn">AdGuard for iOS</a>
		</div>
		<p>Filter lists I recommend:</p>
		<ul class="keep-ls">
			<li><a href="https://github.com/hagezi/dns-blocklists">HaGeZi Ultimate blocklists</a></li>
			<li>uBlock filters (built in)</li>
			<li><a href="https://adguard.com/kb/en/general/ad-filtering/adguard-filters/">AdGuard filters</a></li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</details>
<details>
	<summary>What other ad blocker test tools do you recommend?</summary>
	<div>
		<p>I built this project to quickly test my own short list of common hosts, with a clean design that anyone can use. Other good tools worth trying:</p>
